“Yes, sir. They should already be on their way now; we gave them time to pack food from the mess hall.” At exactly 05:00, Exodus assembled at the vehicle depot. Captain Xiao stood on a box and began to speak.
“We will head to the I-131 frontline base 50 miles outside of Ianlos City. We will support the ongoing siege operation and then launch an attack on Ianlos City to clear out the insurgents. We will use this as our base to advance into the mountains.” Captain Xiao explained. “Take your squad and prepare to depart.”
The platoon dispersed, with each squad taking a tank under the leadership of their squad leader. Kolen climbed onto a tank at the front of the convoy and sat with Nimich, Kress, and two new recruits. Kolen remembered they had just arrived a few days ago, but he didn’t know them well. He sat on the edge of the tank, his legs hanging down, adjusting his backpack and radio equipment, and connecting it to his earphones and throat microphone.
“Hey, Kolen, did Harris still have Snowball?” Nimich asked after they had settled in.
“You mean the chicken he stole?” Kolen recalled the scene from that morning when they had stolen a chicken from the farm. “Yeah, I’m sure of it.”
Kolen looked at another tank and saw Harris and his squad. He caught a glimpse of a small chicken peeking around from behind Harris's backpack.
"Yeah, he's still keeping that chicken," Kolen answered. At that moment, the tank's turret hatch creaked open, and the commander appeared before them.
"All tanks have departed," the commander calmly and clearly said into his earpiece. The armored platoon's tanks and Stryker armored vehicles roared to life and began moving forward. Kolen's Kroneo tank released the brakes and moved forward, entering formation. The tanks formed a wedge formation as they crossed the Itanyia Plain. The winter blizzards had frozen the wetlands and forests, but the mud still remained.
About an hour later, a new recruit (Kolen remembered his name was Orson) spoke up, "Lieutenant, have you been on the front lines since the war started?"
"Yeah, I've been here since the Firestorm operation started," Kolen replied. "We thought the fighting would end within a few weeks, but... we underestimated them."
“岂止是低估。”尼米奇也加入了谈话。“他们的武器和兵力都超出了我们的预期。他们在头两周就击落了 UFS Revenant，上个月又击落了 Erebus。该死，我们应该能在路上看到它。”
“好吧，我会勇敢地为联邦而战。”奥森坚定地说道，“我不会被那些恐怖分子吓倒的。”
“你现在是这么说，但据我所见，大多数像你这样刚成年的新兵蛋子，一听到枪声就吓得屁滚尿流。”克雷斯说道。
“那我们走着瞧吧，”科伦笑着说。奥森没有再说话。
“Exodus 副指挥官！Exodus 指挥官！”科伦的无线电设备发出呼叫。“我们在右前方 20 度 350 码处发现热信号。”
Kolen climbed onto the tank and put on his optical goggles. After switching to thermal imaging mode, he saw the heat signature in the distance.
"Yes, I see them," Kolen said into his throat microphone.
"Are they enemies?" asked another new recruit, Natalie.
"Can't tell yet," Kolen said, opening the microphone. "Exodus Platoon, don't open fire unless attacked. Just draw them out first."
As they got closer, the faint heat signature transformed from a blurred spot into a clearer outline. One of them ran to somewhere, picked up something, and then ran back to the small ridge. Then, these people crouched down and took up firing positions.
"We've encountered enemies!" Captain Xiao shouted over the radio when tracer fire erupted from the ridge. Bullets pinged against the tank's side, and the assault team members leapt down from the tank and took cover behind it. A anti-tank missile screamed toward them, hitting the ground behind the tank formation and exploding, sending shrapnel that struck one of the tanks. Another missile hit the side of an APS-Cerberus Stryker armored vehicle and exploded. After the ammunition殉爆, the crew members in the vehicle scrambled out to seek cover.
"Iron 1-2 and 1-3, 25 degrees to the right, 300 yards. Fire!" The tank platoon leader shouted over the radio. The main guns of Iron 1-2 and 1-3 roared to life, firing shells toward the ridge, sending up clouds of dirt and debris into the air.
"Send out reconnaissance drones!" Knox shouted, still observing the ridge through his binoculars. The rear hatch of a "Hellhound" opened, and a soldier emerged without carrying any weapons, wearing special headphones. He shouted into a square microphone, and two "Sentinel" robots emerged in response. Their slender metal arms and legs moved forward rapidly, running quickly. The robots were equipped with weapons, but they were all strapped to their backs.
"Kill or capture?" Kress asked while observing.
"It looks like they want to capture the enemy alive," Kolen guessed. He saw the two Sentinel robots disappear into the ashes and smoke. Screams and gunfire echoed from the ridge, but it soon calmed down. After a while, the two Sentinel robots returned, dragging a person with their boots leaving a trail in the dirt. Upon reaching the safe area, the robots threw the prisoner to the ground, where he crashed into the mud and snow, whimpering in pain.
He struggled to stand up, and Captain Xiao approached. Captain Xiao turned to one of the sentry robots. “How many people?”
“Three dead, sir.” The sentry robot replied. “The rest have fled on foot.”
Captain Xiao nodded and turned to talk to Kolen and Kress, who were standing nearby. “Can the two of you take this person away?”
